    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-05-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="212"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d212">
                <head>212. Letter From Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_MGGC1" type="from"
                        >Marshall</persName> to Senator <persName type="to">Chan Gurney</persName>
                    <note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d212fn0">Source: National Archives and Records
                        Administration, RG 59, Records of the Department of State, Decimal File
                        1945–49, 101.5/5–547. No classification marking. Drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_MGGC1">Marshall</persName>. A note on the source text reads:
                        “Delivered by hand 5/6/47.”</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-05-05"
                        >May 5, 1947</date>.</dateline>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Senator</hi>: This is to confirm the message I asked
                    General <persName>Carter</persName>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d212fn1">Brigadier <persName corresp="#p_MGGC1">General
                            Marshall Carter</persName>, Secretary <persName corresp="#p_MGGC1"
                            >Marshall</persName>’s Special Assistant.</note> to pass on to you
                    Friday afternoon.<note n="2" xml:id="d212fn2">Presumably Friday, May 2.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The legislation regarding the <gloss target="#t_CIG1">CIG</gloss> reflects the
                    unchanged status of the agreement reached in February by the Secretaries of War
                    and Navy and myself.<note n="3" xml:id="d212fn3">No documents concerning this
                        agreement, and no other references to it, have been found.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Faithfully yours,<note n="4" xml:id="d212fn4">Printed from an unsigned
                        copy.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
